comments: VanVleet (TOR) briefly places and retracts his arms from Simmons (BKN) during the pick and the contact is marginal.
O'Neale (BKN) is moving alongside Siakam's (TOR) path when he absorbs the incidental body contact at the end of the drive.
Durant (BKN) legally contests Anunoby?s (TOR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Claxton (BKN) is firming up on his right foot in Barnes?s (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs as the players come together during the pick.
Trent Jr. (TOR) is retreating from Irving (BKN) when marginal contact occurs at the start of Irving's drive.
Barnes (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Trent Jr. (TOR) establishes himself in Simmons' (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs as Simmons (BKN) attempts to move over the pick.
Simmons (BKN) legally contests Trent Jr.'s (TOR) driving shot attempt and Trent Jr. loses his balance when he returns to the floor.
O'Neale (BKN) establishes himself in Barnes?s (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs as O'Neale is firming up.
O'Neale (BKN) turns his body and steps towards the hoop when marginal contact occurs with Anunoby (TOR), who is trailing Durant (BKN).
Trent Jr. (TOR) establishes himself in Simmons?s (BKN) path and incidental contact occurs as the players come together and disengage.
VanVleet (TOR) establishes himself in O'Neale's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet (TOR) disengages after the pick.
VanVleet's (TOR) off-arm comes out  and makes incidental contact with O'Neale (BKN), whose momentum carries him into the paint.
Durant (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
VanVleet (TOR) lightly brushes Irving's (BKN) right arm and Irving continues to dribble through the marginal contact.
Simmons (BKN) and Trent Jr. (TOR) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen dissolves.
Durant (BKN) initiates contact with Siakam?s (TOR) arm, which affects the driving shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) and Barnes (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
VanVleet (TOR) initiates contact with Durant?s (BKN) arm and affects Durant?s (BKN) control of the ball.
Anunoby (TOR) and Durant (BKN) engage during the inbounds and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.

VanVleet (TOR) makes contact with the ball and part of Durant's (BKN) left hand that is on the ball, which dislodges it from Durant's possession. Any arm contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
